Evaluate the completeness of the essential entries (such as, but not limited to, the period covered by the policy) required in performance and warranty securities posted in favor of the LGU before its acceptance to ensure its enforceability; and
Ensure compliance the provisions of 2016 R-IRR of R.A. No. 9184 as to the performance and warranty securities.

We recommended that Management:

Maintain a ledger of all incoming and outgoing supplies/goods;
Adopt the use of Requisition Issue Slip (RIS) in each issuance of supplies; 
Consolidate the RIS into Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) and furnish the Municipal Accountant the same to facilitate the timely and accurate presentation of the inventories on hand in the FS;
Submit the properly accomplished Report on Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) as prescribed by existing regulations to the accounting department and the COA; and
Maintain a Subsidiary Ledger Card (SLC) per stock number.

We recommended that Management:
Ensure continued prompt remittance to the GSIS of the monthly contributions (Government and Personal Share), loan amortizations, and employee compensation premium;
Through the AAO, timely and regularly manifest in writing to the GSIS by means of coordinating monthly thru e-mail with the said agency the need to resolve the recurring concern where its electronic bill is not updated despite LGU’s diligence in the timely updating of employee service records;
Warrant the timely recording in the accounting system of amounts withheld and remitted to the GSIS; and
Ensure compliance with Sections 5 and 6 (b) of R.A.  No. 8291.

We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

For monitoring and disclosure, require the information system admin to enhance the aging module of the accounting system to reflect fairly the age of accounts;
Impose strict compliance with the rules and regulations on the proper granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances;
Require all officials concerned to immediately refund/settle in full their outstanding cash advances; and
Enforce Section 128 of P.D. No. 1445 or erring personnel.

We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

Require the accounting system admin to improve the aging module;
Submit the aging of accounts payable as part of the FS each year;
Review and determine the validity of long outstanding payable accounts; and
Revert back to the General Fund (GF) payables without legal claim in accordance with Section 98 of P.D. 1445.

We recommended that Management take the following courses of action: 

Ensure that necessary adjusting entries for the remittances of taxes withheld from all funds of the LGU are made timely and correctly, thus, avoiding abnormal negative or debit balances of the accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2015-009;
Posting of the transactions, whether withholding or remittances, should be made in a timely manner;
When warranted, consider to reinforce the present staff who uses the accounting system being utilized by the Accounting unit by additional trained staff to regulate the volume of work to ensure that no transactions are inadvertently overlooked (such as the necessary transfer of funds and adjustment of Due to BIR accounts under different funds); and
Ensure that BIR returns and similar important files are kept properly.

We recommended that Management take the following courses of action: 

Trace the source of the differences between the total amount of monthly premium contributions and loan amortizations withheld with the corresponding total amount remitted during CY 2019 and prior years and ensure that the necessary actions be taken to effect the proper adjustment, whether by appropriately making refunds or remitting such differences;
Ensure that transactions are recorded timely in the system and are posted correctly in the proper ledger accounts;
When warranted, consider to reinforce the present staff who uses the accounting system being utilized by the Accounting unit by additional trained staff to regulate the volume of work to ensure that no transactions are delayed and erroneously posted; and
Enhance its compliance with the provisions of R.A. No. 9679 and pertinent HDMF Circular with regard to withholding and remittance of monthly contributions and loan amortizations to the HDMF.

