We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

Ensure that Purchase Order (PO) is issued timely and the delivery terms specified therein shall not contradict with what was provided in the contract and other documents issued forming integral part of such contract such as the Notice to Proceed (NTP), if any;
Warrant that delivery terms in the procurement of goods should be specific, clear and consistent. Ultimately, the compliance to the same should be enjoined; 
Reinforce the BAC Secretariat with additional full time staff to avoid oversight in the timing of issuance of important procurement related documents; and
Ensure the LGU’s compliance with the issued guidelines on the implementation of programs, projects, and activities funded by different NGAs.

We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

Require the Accounting Unit to determine accordingly to which the unused balances relate, whether to fund transferred by Source Agencies or LGU counterpart. Afterwards, immediately return the unused balance referring to fund transferred by the Source Agency to the SA concerned or revert back to the GF those referring to the LGU counterpart, in accordance with COA Circular No. 94-013 and Letter (b), Section 418 of Administrative Order (A.O.) No. 270, respectively; 
Ensure that the Accounting Unit, include the description of the accounts related to each project in the subsidiary ledgers, indicating therein the name of specific project, the SA and to which national program it relates (e.g. Construction of Evacuation Center at Barangay Tabas/DILG/ Assistance to Disadvantaged Municipalities [ADM] CY 2017) to avoid ambiguity and enhance monitoring;
If practicable, maintain a monitoring schedule on the utilization of funds intended for specific projects requiring LGU counterpart, in order to determine to which the unused balances of the completed projects relate, whether to the fund transferred by the Source Agencies or LGU counterpart; and
Strictly adhere with the pertinent provisions of COA Circular No. 94-013 and Letter (b), Section 418 of A.O. No. 270, with regard to the appropriate and timely disposition of unused balances relating to completed projects funded by different Source Agencies.

