We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

Judiciously plan the prioritization of projects by considering the following:
Highly consider the feasibility of the identified location, if practicable identify also equally feasible alternative location, in the prioritization of project to avoid delays in its implementation;

Ensure to anticipate, at the earliest stage of project prioritization, the material surrounding facts which will eventually affect the timely implementation of the project (such as the pre-requisite requirement for electricity installation and the availability of qualified supplier);

Ensure that amounts to be appropriated for PPAs should be close to its funding requirements, if not, exact, in order to ensure effective and efficient use of the 20 per cent DF, by referring to the prepared POW in case of infrastructure projects, and in case of loan amortizations, based on the Amortization Schedule provided by the bank-creditor; and

Ensure effective utilization of the 20 per cent by limiting the prioritization of projects as to its necessity and urgency of implementation to avoid funds being tied to projects which eventually will not be implemented.

Coordinate and advise the beneficiary Barangay, in case of change on intention in the implementation of the prioritized projects, to timely and properly manifest such intention to the Municipal Development Council (MDC) for their appropriate action to ensure optimal utilization of the 20 per cent DF;

In the implementation of the prioritized PPAs, ensure to anticipate the effects of bad weather condition in its implementation schedule in order to avoid non-implementation;

Enhance the utilization of the 20 per cent of the IRA as prescribed in DBM-DILG JMC No. 2017-01.

We recommend that Management take the following courses of action:

Direct the contractors to always submit a dated request for inspection to the LGU and a dated Statement of Work Accomplished (SWA) for every progress payment, and most importantly, on the final payment, as corroborating evidence that the works were accomplished within the agreed contract time;

Require the Municipal Engineer to timely and strictly monitor the implementation of projects in accordance with the agreed contract time;

Adhere to Section 7 of Annex E of the 2016 R-IRR of R.A. No. 9184 on the inspection of project once it reaches an accomplishment of 95 per cent of the contract amount. Likewise, ensure that projects are inspected on its scheduled/targeted dates of completion in order to reasonably determine whether the project was actually completed on such date, if not, at least, determine the percentage of unfinished work which will be used as basis in the computation of liquidated damages, when warranted; and

Issue a certificate of completion for each completed project which shall serve as reasonable basis of the actual completion date of such project.

